Let me help you.

150
00:07:26.321 --> 00:07:27.489 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Me, too.

151
00:07:27.572 --> 00:07:29.658 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Just gather it up
with your hand,

152
00:07:29.741 --> 00:07:32.827 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
and roll the snow
into a ball like this.

153
00:07:32.911 --> 00:07:34.079 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
[gasps]

154
00:07:34.162 --> 00:07:36.623 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Uh, hold on.

155
00:07:36.706 --> 00:07:38.208 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
This is going to work.

156
00:07:38.291 --> 00:07:39.542 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
[grunts]

157
00:07:39.626 --> 00:07:41.294 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
[groans]

158
00:07:41.419 --> 00:07:43.338 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
[sighs]

159
00:07:43.421 --> 00:07:44.756 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
It didn't work.

160
00:07:44.839 --> 00:07:46.049 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
[Bean groans]

161
00:07:47.676 --> 00:07:50.971 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
This snow doesn't make snowmen.
That's a clue.

162
00:07:51.096 --> 00:07:53.807 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
It doesn't really do anything
that snow does.

163
00:07:55.058 --> 00:07:56.476 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
It's not cold,

164
00:07:56.559 --> 00:07:59.688 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
and when I rub the snowflake,
it should melt.

165
00:08:03.149 --> 00:08:05.193 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
[Toby]
And there's something in here,

166
00:08:05.276 --> 00:08:06.736 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
a little brown spot.

167
00:08:06.820 --> 00:08:09.614 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Snowflakes don't have
little brown spots.

168
00:08:09.698 --> 00:08:11.950 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
I don't think
these are snowflakes.

169
00:08:12.033 --> 00:08:13.827 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
How can it not be snow?

170
00:08:13.910 --> 00:08:16.287 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
It's white and fluffy
and falling from the sky.

171
00:08:16.371 --> 00:08:18.915 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Teri's right.
This snow isn't cold.

172
00:08:19.040 --> 00:08:22.335 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
And it's supposed
to fall from clouds, but look.

173
00:08:22.460 --> 00:08:24.838 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
There's not a cloud in the sky.

174
00:08:26.214 --> 00:08:28.925 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
You're right. This snow
is blowing in on the wind,

175
00:08:29.009 --> 00:08:31.469 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
and it's all coming
from over there.

176
00:08:32.262 --> 00:08:35.682 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Then that's the way we're going.
Come on, everybody!

177
00:08:42.063 --> 00:08:44.733 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
It's snowing really hard!

178
00:08:44.816 --> 00:08:47.444 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
We should turn back!

179
00:08:47.527 --> 00:08:50.822 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
No! Keep going!

180
00:08:50.905 --> 00:08:53.158 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Why are you all yelling?

181
00:08:53.241 --> 00:08:54.743 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
[chuckles]

182
00:08:54.826 --> 00:08:58.038 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
You're supposed to yell
in snowstorms, aren't you?

183
00:08:58.121 --> 00:09:00.665 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
I don't think
this is a snowstorm.

184
00:09:09.966 --> 00:09:11.468 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
[Jay]
Hey, it's summer!

185
00:09:11.551 --> 00:09:12.510 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
I can't believe it.

186
00:09:12.594 --> 00:09:14.429 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
You guys made it summer again.

187
00:09:14.554 --> 00:09:18.099 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
All we did was follow the facts,
and they brought us here.

188
00:09:19.142 --> 00:09:20.852 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Just as I suspected,

189
00:09:20.935 --> 00:09:22.228 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
it's not winter yet.

190
00:09:22.353 --> 00:09:23.813 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Each of these snowflakes

191
00:09:23.897 --> 00:09:26.399 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
is carrying a seed
from these cottonwood trees.

192
00:09:26.483 --> 00:09:29.110 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Remember those brown spots
Toby found?

193
00:09:29.194 --> 00:09:30.445 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Those are the seeds.

194
00:09:30.528 --> 00:09:33.490 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
So what's all
the white stuff for?

195
00:09:33.573 --> 00:09:36.242 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
The cottony bit
makes the seed float

196
00:09:36.367 --> 00:09:38.703 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
so the wind can carry them
to new places

197
00:09:38.787 --> 00:09:40.413 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
to make new cottonwood trees.

198
00:09:40.497 --> 00:09:44.000 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
So this isn't real snow.
It's summer snow.

199
00:09:44.125 --> 00:09:46.086 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
[laughs]
Exactly.

200
00:09:46.169 --> 00:09:48.505 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Cottonwood trees
only do this in summer.

201
00:09:48.588 --> 00:09:50.924 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Which means I get to put on

202
00:09:51.007 --> 00:09:53.134 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
my Summer Spectacular
show after all!

203
00:09:53.218 --> 00:09:55.011 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Yippee!

204
00:09:59.557 --> 00:10:01.351 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Prepare to be amazed.

205
00:10:01.434 --> 00:10:05.313 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Presenting
Jay's Summer Spectacular,

206
00:10:05.396 --> 00:10:07.774 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
starring Jay!

207
00:10:09.400 --> 00:10:12.445 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
-[cheering]
-All right, Jay!

208
00:10:12.529 --> 00:10:16.032 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Thank you. The first act
of my Summer Spectacular

209
00:10:16.116 --> 00:10:19.994 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
is called "ode to the fluffy
cottonwood seeds of summer."

210
00:10:32.632 --> 00:10:34.592 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
[cheering]

211
00:10:34.717 --> 00:10:36.803 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
All right, Jay!

212
00:10:41.599 --> 00:10:43.143 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
[chirping]

213
00:10:46.187 --> 00:10:48.731 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Say, "Snowflakes"!

214
00:10:48.815 --> 00:10:50.316 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
-Snowflakes!
-Snowflakes!

215
00:10:50.400 --> 00:10:51.401 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
[camera clicks]

216
00:10:54.571 --> 00:10:56.823 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
These sure look like snowflakes.

217
00:10:56.906 --> 00:10:59.659 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
But it shouldn't have been
snowing on a summer day.

218
00:10:59.742 --> 00:11:02.412 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
You're right.
It didn't make sense.

219
00:11:02.495 --> 00:11:04.330 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Until we followed the facts

220
00:11:04.414 --> 00:11:06.499 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
straight
to the cottonwood trees.

221
00:11:06.624 --> 00:11:09.294 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Time to close this case.

222
