♪ <i>Follow the facts ♪</i>

225
00:11:21.681 --> 00:11:23.057 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
♪ <i>The case is now solved ♪</i>

226
00:11:24.475 --> 00:11:27.020 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
♪ <i>We are detective Toby and Teri ♪</i>

227
00:11:30.013 --> 00:11:32.271 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
[together] "The Case
of the Suspicious Snowflakes"

228
00:11:32.372 --> 00:11:34.235 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
is officially closed.

229
00:11:36.613 --> 00:11:38.615 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
[saxophone playing]

230
00:11:44.996 --> 00:11:46.748 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:10.00% 
Where is everybody?

231
00:11:46.831 --> 00:11:48.333 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:10.00% 
[Teri]
Here we are.

232
00:11:50.376 --> 00:11:53.213 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:10.00% 
Millie's Acorn Springs Band
is ready for rehearsal.

233
00:11:53.338 --> 00:11:57.342 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
One bagpipe ready to, um...

234
00:11:57.425 --> 00:11:58.343 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
pipe.

235
00:11:58.426 --> 00:12:01.346 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
[plays bagpipe]

236
00:12:01.429 --> 00:12:02.889 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
I've got my violin.

237
00:12:04.432 --> 00:12:07.644 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
[plays violin]

238
00:12:08.311 --> 00:12:11.481 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
[bongos playing]

239
00:12:12.482 --> 00:12:14.400 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Just call me Bongo Bean.

240
00:12:14.484 --> 00:12:16.486 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
[maracas shaking]

241
00:12:18.529 --> 00:12:20.573 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
And I'm ready with my maracas.

242
00:12:20.657 --> 00:12:22.992 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Perfect. Now there's nothing

243
00:12:23.076 --> 00:12:25.453 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
keeping us from fame
and fortune except...

244
00:12:26.621 --> 00:12:28.498 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Rumy. Where is he?

245
00:12:28.623 --> 00:12:30.124 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Here I am.

246
00:12:31.125 --> 00:12:32.752 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Where's your instrument?

247
00:12:32.835 --> 00:12:35.338 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
I don't have one.

248
00:12:35.463 --> 00:12:38.383 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
That's okay.
You don't need an instrument.

249
00:12:38.508 --> 00:12:41.386 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Last time I checked,
pigs are pretty good at oinking.

250
00:12:41.469 --> 00:12:42.679 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Why don't you try that?

251
00:12:42.762 --> 00:12:44.389 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Ha! Really?

252
00:12:44.472 --> 00:12:46.599 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Oh, that's a great idea.

253
00:12:46.683 --> 00:12:49.185 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Okay. Let's see how it sounds.

254
00:12:49.310 --> 00:12:50.478 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
From the top.

255
00:12:50.561 --> 00:12:52.981 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
And one and two and...

256
00:12:53.106 --> 00:12:54.649 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
[band playing]

257
00:12:54.732 --> 00:12:56.776 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
[snorting]

258
00:12:59.988 --> 00:13:03.324 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
[shrill]
♪ <i>Oink oink oink oink! ♪</i>

259
00:13:05.910 --> 00:13:08.204 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
That did not sound good.

260
00:13:08.288 --> 00:13:11.374 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Uh, you know what?
I-I can just listen.

261
00:13:11.457 --> 00:13:13.418 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Th-That'll be fun, too.

262
00:13:13.543 --> 00:13:16.921 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
No. This band is for everyone.

263
00:13:17.005 --> 00:13:21.175 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Toby, Teri, do you think you can
make something for Rumy to play?

264
00:13:21.301 --> 00:13:22.510 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Sure we can,

265
00:13:22.593 --> 00:13:25.305 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
if we can figure out
how instruments make sound.

266
00:13:25.388 --> 00:13:27.807 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Sounds like we've got a case.

267
00:13:27.932 --> 00:13:29.517 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Will you excuse us?

268
00:13:29.600 --> 00:13:31.769 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
To the treehouse!

269
00:13:32.937 --> 00:13:34.230 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
[camera clicks]

270
00:13:37.442 --> 00:13:38.735 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Our instruments are all made

271
00:13:38.818 --> 00:13:41.070 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
of things
you can find in the forest.

272
00:13:41.154 --> 00:13:45.575 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
I wonder, how we can get things like
this leaf and stick to make music?

273
00:13:45.658 --> 00:13:47.910 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
It's a mystery that
we've gotta figure out

274
00:13:47.994 --> 00:13:50.955 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
so we can make Rumy
an amazing instrument all his own.

275
00:13:51.080 --> 00:13:54.792 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
If we don't,
Rumy can't be in the band.

276
00:13:54.876 --> 00:13:56.669 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
There's a lot at stake.

277
00:13:56.794 --> 00:13:59.881 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
There always is, little brother.
There always is.

278
00:14:00.006 --> 00:14:01.883 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Let's do this.

279
00:14:05.595 --> 00:14:07.555 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
♪ <i>Looking for clues ♪</i>

280
