♪ <i>Check the scene ♪</i>

281
00:14:13.644 --> 00:14:15.646 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
<i>♪ Any cases ♪</i>

282
00:14:17.565 --> 00:14:19.442 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
♪ <i>Little detectives ♪</i>

283
00:14:20.735 --> 00:14:22.528 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
♪ <i>Can solve it ♪</i>

284
00:14:26.240 --> 00:14:28.951 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
[together]
Let's ace this case!

285
00:14:31.518 --> 00:14:33.426 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Great, move it over there.

286
00:14:33.539 --> 00:14:34.957 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
[Teri]
Beatrice...

287
00:14:36.501 --> 00:14:38.086 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
how are you?

288
00:14:38.211 --> 00:14:40.171 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Busy as always.

289
00:14:40.296 --> 00:14:42.757 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
We've got to get our dam ready
for the winter.

290
00:14:42.840 --> 00:14:44.634 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
So, what can I do you for?

291
00:14:44.759 --> 00:14:48.679 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Toby and Teri are going
to make me a musical instrument.

292
00:14:48.805 --> 00:14:51.057 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
If you guys have detailed plans,

293
00:14:51.182 --> 00:14:53.476 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
we can build you
whatever you want.

294
00:14:53.601 --> 00:14:55.603 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Do you guys ever make music?

295
00:14:55.728 --> 00:14:58.898 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
That's all we do
when we're not building things.

296
00:14:58.981 --> 00:14:59.982 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Check it out.

297
00:15:00.066 --> 00:15:03.903 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Hey, guys, let's play 'em
something snappy!

298
00:15:05.988 --> 00:15:08.199 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
[playing percussion]

299
00:15:09.700 --> 00:15:11.869 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
I love this sound.

300
00:15:11.953 --> 00:15:14.455 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Oh ho! This is great!

301
00:15:16.791 --> 00:15:20.420 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Yeah! That's why
I love playing drums!

302
00:15:25.633 --> 00:15:26.717 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
What?

303
00:15:26.801 --> 00:15:28.136 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
[sighs]

304
00:15:28.219 --> 00:15:30.680 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
We've already got
a drum in the band.

305
00:15:30.805 --> 00:15:33.307 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
I need to find something else.

306
00:15:37.770 --> 00:15:40.189 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Oh, I found this.
[laughs]

307
00:15:40.273 --> 00:15:42.024 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
It's a hollow stick.

308
00:15:42.108 --> 00:15:45.361 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
If you put pebbles in it,
you can make it rattle.

309
00:15:45.445 --> 00:15:46.362 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
[laughs]

310
00:15:46.446 --> 00:15:47.822 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
[shaking]

311
00:15:47.905 --> 00:15:50.575 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Ah! That's pretty neat.

312
00:15:50.658 --> 00:15:52.952 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
But that's the sound
my maracas make.

313
00:15:53.035 --> 00:15:54.412 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
[maracas shaking]
See?

314
00:15:56.497 --> 00:15:58.708 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Oh, you're right.

315
00:15:58.833 --> 00:16:02.420 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
So is there
something else I can play?

316
00:16:02.503 --> 00:16:05.756 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
The beavers's tails
were like Bean's drum...

317
00:16:05.882 --> 00:16:09.969 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
and the hollow stick sounded
just like Jay's maracas.

318
00:16:10.094 --> 00:16:13.347 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
We have to find Rumy
a brand-new way to make music.

319
00:16:13.431 --> 00:16:15.933 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
[moose bellows]

320
00:16:16.017 --> 00:16:17.894 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
How about a sound like that?

321
00:16:18.019 --> 00:16:22.190 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Yeah. That's awesome!
Where's that coming from?

322
00:16:23.191 --> 00:16:26.110 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Hi, everybody.
What's going on?

323
00:16:26.194 --> 00:16:29.989 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Toby and Teri are going
to make me a musical instrument.

324
00:16:30.072 --> 00:16:32.783 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Maybe one that does
what you just did.

325
00:16:32.867 --> 00:16:33.951 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Uhh!

326
00:16:34.035 --> 00:16:35.953 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
How did you make that sound?

327
00:16:36.037 --> 00:16:38.498 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
It was the loudest thing
I've ever heard.

328
00:16:38.581 --> 00:16:42.043 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
I don't think I could do that
if I tried. Ohhh!

329
00:16:42.168 --> 00:16:45.254 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
The trick is to fill your lungs
like a balloon.

330
00:16:45.338 --> 00:16:46.547 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
[inhales]

331
00:16:46.631 --> 00:16:48.758 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Then let it out
through your nose.

332
00:16:48.841 --> 00:16:51.886 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
[bellows]

333
00:16:53.554 --> 00:16:54.680 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
[playing bagpipe]

334
00:16:54.805 --> 00:16:56.432 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
[bellows]

335
00:16:56.557 --> 00:16:57.892 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
[playing bagpipe]

336
00:16:58.017 --> 00:17:01.062 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
[bellows]

337
00:17:01.145 --> 00:17:02.313 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
What's wrong?

338
00:17:02.396 --> 00:17:05.900 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
The Acorn Springs Band
already has an instrument

339
00:17:05.983 --> 00:17:10.154 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
that makes moose sounds,
your bagpipes.

340
00:17:11.113 --> 00:17:12.114 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
You're right.

341
00:17:12.198 --> 00:17:15.117 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
That's okay.
We'll just try something else.

342
00:17:15.201 --> 00:17:18.996 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Can you think of anyone around
here who also makes music?

343
00:17:19.121 --> 00:17:21.332 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
You should talk to the crickets.

344
00:17:21.415 --> 00:17:23.834 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
I love the sounds they make.

345
00:17:24.961 --> 00:17:27.505 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Crickets make beautiful music.

346
00:17:27.588 --> 00:17:31.509 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
I always hear crickets
over here in the tall grass.

347
00:17:31.592 --> 00:17:34.637 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
[cricket chirping]

348
00:17:34.720 --> 00:17:36.681 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Hey! Here's one.

349
00:17:38.432 --> 00:17:39.767 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Hello, little cricket.

350
00:17:39.892 --> 00:17:43.104 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
She makes music
by rubbing her legs together.

351
00:17:43.187 --> 00:17:44.730 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Can you do that again?

352
00:17:44.814 --> 00:17:46.357 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
[chirping]

353
00:17:46.440 --> 00:17:48.401 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
[Millie]
The cricket's legs vibrate.

354
00:17:48.484 --> 00:17:50.861 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
That's what makes the music.

355
00:17:52.113 --> 00:17:54.240 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
[playing violin]

356
00:17:55.283 --> 00:17:57.285 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
My violin works the same way.

357
00:17:57.368 --> 00:17:59.412 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
I pull the bow
across the strings,

358
00:17:59.537 --> 00:18:00.746 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
and they make music.

359
00:18:01.581 --> 00:18:04.750 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
So even if I could
do that with my legs,

360
00:18:04.834 --> 00:18:08.629 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
we've already got
that sound in the band.

361
00:18:09.380 --> 00:18:12.508 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Don't worry, Rumy.
We won't give up.

362
00:18:12.592 --> 00:18:16.470 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
And using the clues we've got
so far, I've got an idea.

363
00:18:16.596 --> 00:18:18.973 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
I've got a sound
that isn't like anything

364
00:18:19.056 --> 00:18:20.600 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
in The Acorn Springs Band.

365
00:18:20.683 --> 00:18:23.394 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
[wind blowing]

366
00:18:23.477 --> 00:18:28.149 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
I come here sometimes to think,
and I always listen to the wind.

367
00:18:29.066 --> 00:18:31.193 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
That's a great sound.

368
00:18:31.277 --> 00:18:34.780 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
[gasps]
I think I could do that.

369
00:18:34.864 --> 00:18:38.034 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Whoooo!

370
00:18:38.117 --> 00:18:40.244 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
[breathless]
Like this?

371
00:18:40.328 --> 00:18:42.913 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
[coughing]

372
00:18:44.665 --> 00:18:46.375 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
I give up.

373
00:18:50.171 --> 00:18:51.547 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
[air whistling]

374
00:18:52.548 --> 00:18:55.593 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Wait! Rumy, did you hear that?

375
00:18:55.676 --> 00:18:57.595 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
[air whistling]
You just made music.

376
00:18:58.846 --> 00:19:01.641 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
[gasps]
How did I do that?

377
00:19:01.724 --> 00:19:03.809 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Let's follow the facts.

378
00:19:03.934 --> 00:19:05.227 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
The wind is blowing...

379
00:19:06.520 --> 00:19:08.648 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
and the tree is hollow.

380
00:19:08.731 --> 00:19:11.317 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
And every time Rumy sits down,

381
00:19:11.400 --> 00:19:14.320 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
he covers one of the holes
in the log.

382
00:19:15.738 --> 00:19:17.782 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
[air whistling]

383
00:19:20.284 --> 00:19:22.078 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
[whistling changes pitch]

384
00:19:23.329 --> 00:19:24.830 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
[whistling changes pitch]

385
00:19:24.914 --> 00:19:26.207 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
[laughs]
This is fun.

386
00:19:26.332 --> 00:19:28.376 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Oh! You guys wanna try?

387
00:19:28.501 --> 00:19:30.419 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
-Sure!
-Sure!

388
00:19:33.130 --> 00:19:35.132 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
[playing melody]

389
00:19:37.176 --> 00:19:40.388 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
[laughs]
That sounds great!

390
00:19:40.513 --> 00:19:41.972 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
[cheering]

391
00:19:49.021 --> 00:19:50.231 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
What is it, Rumy?

392
00:19:50.314 --> 00:19:54.902 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
This is great,
but it's too big to move,

393
00:19:54.985 --> 00:19:58.322 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
so I don't have
an instrument again.

394
00:19:58.406 --> 00:20:01.826 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Toby, now that we know
how the log makes music,

395
00:20:01.909 --> 00:20:05.871 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
can you make Rumy something
just like it, but smaller?

396
00:20:08.332 --> 00:20:09.458 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Sure.

397
00:20:12.294 --> 00:20:14.463 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Can you make some holes in this?

398
00:20:14.547 --> 00:20:18.843 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
A big one here and a bunch
of little ones along here.

399
00:20:19.885 --> 00:20:22.763 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
[laughs]
You got it.

400
00:20:27.893 --> 00:20:29.228 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Thanks.

401
00:20:29.311 --> 00:20:33.107 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Now just blow across here,
like you were the wind.

402
00:20:33.190 --> 00:20:35.317 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Okay.

403
00:20:40.364 --> 00:20:41.449 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
[plays note]

404
00:20:41.824 --> 00:20:43.200 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Hey!

405
00:20:43.284 --> 00:20:45.619 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
-It's working!
-[cheering]

406
00:20:45.703 --> 00:20:47.788 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
And it's a sound all your own.

407
00:20:49.165 --> 00:20:52.877 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
[plays melody]

408
00:20:53.002 --> 00:20:55.546 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Now we've really got a band.

409
00:20:55.629 --> 00:20:58.716 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
-[cheering]
-Yay! Yay!

410
00:20:58.841 --> 00:21:00.843 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
[audience murmuring]

411
00:21:08.601 --> 00:21:10.352 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
[band playing]

412
00:21:32.708 --> 00:21:34.710 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
[flute solo]

413
00:21:39.799 --> 00:21:42.176 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
-[cheering]
-[Beatrice] Ah, bravo! Bravo!

414
00:21:42.259 --> 00:21:44.303 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
-[moose bellows]
-[laughing]

415
00:21:44.428 --> 00:21:45.554 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
[Millie]
Thank you.

416
00:21:45.679 --> 00:21:50.226 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
We're so glad you came to see
the Acorn Springs Band.

417
00:21:54.230 --> 00:21:56.190 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Say, "Music!"

418
00:21:56.273 --> 00:21:57.566 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
-Music!
-Music!

419
00:21:57.650 --> 00:21:58.651 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
[camera clicks]

420
00:22:01.278 --> 00:22:05.074 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
We helped our friend be a part
of the Acorn Springs Band.

421
00:22:05.199 --> 00:22:08.077 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
And we learned a new way
to make a musical instrument.

